{"title_page": "Wynnum Manly Ward", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2019}}\n{{Infobox Australian Electorate|federal=no|name=Wynnum Manly Ward|image=|imagesize=|caption=|created=|mp=Peter Cumming|mp-party=[[Australian Labor Party (Queensland Branch)|Labor]]|namesake=[[Wynnum, Queensland|Wynnum]], [[Manly, Queensland|Manly]]|electors=24,484|electors_year=[[2016 Brisbane City Council election|2016]]|area=}}\nThe '''Wynnum Manly Ward''' is a [[Brisbane City Council]] [[Ward (electoral subdivision)|ward]] covering [[Wynnum, Queensland|Wynnum]], [[Wynnum West, Queensland|Wynnum West]], [[Manly, Queensland|Manly]], [[Lota, Queensland|Lota]], [[Lytton, Queensland|Lytton]], [[Port of Brisbane]], and part of [[Manly West, Queensland|Manly West]].<ref name=\"BCC\">{{cite web|url=https://www.brisbane.qld.gov.au/about-council/governance-strategy/councillors-wards/wynnum-manly-ward|title=Wynnum Manly Ward|website=Brisbane City Council|publisher=Brisbane City Council|accessdate=11 March 2017}}</ref>\n\n== Councillors for Wynnum Manly Ward ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! colspan=\"2\" |Member\n!Party\n!Term\n|-\n|{{Australian party style|Nationalist}}|&nbsp;\n|[[Bill Dart]]\n|[[National Party (Queensland, 1917)|Nationalist]]\n|1925\u20131931\n|-\n| {{Australian party style|Independent}} |&nbsp;\n|[[John William Greene]]\n|[[Independent politician|Independent]]\n|1931\u20131934\n|-\n|{{Australian party style|UAP}}|&nbsp;\n|[[Bill Dart]]\n|[[United Australia Party \u2013 Queensland|United Australia]]\n|1934\u20131938\n|-\n|{{Australian party style|Protestant Labor}}|&nbsp;\n|Ralph Powell\n|[[Protestant Labor Party|Protestant Labor]]\n|1938\u20131940\n|-\n|{{Australian party style|UAP}}|&nbsp;\n| rowspan=\"2\" |Willie Howard\n|[[United Australia Party \u2013 Queensland|United Australia]]\n|1940\u20131941\n|-\n|{{Australian party style|Liberal}}|&nbsp;\n|[[Liberal Party of Australia (Queensland Division)|Liberal]]\n|1941-1952\n|-\n|{{Australian party style|Labor}}|&nbsp;\n|George 