 government's official tartan registry}}\n\n{{Scottish clans}}\n{{Scotland topics}}\n{{fabric}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Scottish clans| ]]\n[[Category:Tartan| ]]\n[[Category:Textile patterns]]\n[[Category:Textile arts of Scotland]]\n[[Category:Scottish design]]\n", "name_user": "Davemck", "label": "safe", "comment": "rename duplicate parm", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tartan"}
{"title_page": "Marilyn Strickland", "text_new": "{{Infobox Mayor\n| name        = Marilyn Strickland\n| image       = Marilyn Strickland (18655920073).jpg \n| caption     = \n| office      = Mayor of [[Tacoma, Washington]]\n| term_start  = January 5, 2010\n| term_end    = January 2, 2018\n| predecessor = [[Bill Baarsma]]\n| successor   = [[Victoria Woodards]]\n| birth_date  = {{birth year and age|1962}}\n| birth_place = [[Seoul]], [[South Korea]]\n| state2      = \n| term_start2 = \n| term_end2   = \n| preceded2   = \n| succeeded2  = \n| death_date  = \n| death_place = \n| party       = [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]\n| spouse      = \n| relations   = \n| children    = \n| residence   = \n| alma_mater  = [[Clark Atlanta University]] <small>([[Master of Business Administration|M.B.A.]])</small><br/>[[University of Washington]] <small>([[Bachelor of Arts|B.A.]])\n| occupation  = \n| profession  = \n| religion    = \n| signature   = \n| website     = \n| footnotes   = \n}}\n\n'''Marilyn Strickland''' (born 1962) is an [[Politics of the United States|American politician]] and former [[Mayor]] of the City of [[Tacoma, Washington]].\n\n== Biography ==\n\nMarylin Strickland was born in [[Seoul]], [[South Korea]] where her father was [[USFK|stationed]]. In 1967 her father was assigned to  [[Fort Lewis]], Washington, and the family moved to Tacoma.\n\nStrickland has worked as a marketing manager for [[Starbucks]] and as an officer in the Tacoma Public Library System. She is a graduate of the [[University of Washington]] and holds a [[Master\u2019s Degree]] in [[Business Administration]] from [[Clark-Atlanta University]].<ref>[http://www.cityoftacoma.org/page.aspx?nid=54#Strickland ''City of Tacoma] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080329124255/http://www.cityoftacoma.org/Page.aspx?nid=54 |date=2008-03-29 }} Accessed 25 October 2012</ref>\n\nShe was elected in 2008 for the [[Tacoma City Council]].<ref>[http://themelononline.com/2009/04/interview-with-marilyn-strickland-tacoma-mayoral-candidate/  ''The Melon Interview with Marylin Strickland''] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090430155719/http://themelononline.com/2009/04/interview-with-marilyn-strickland-tacoma-mayoral-candidate/ |date=2009-04-30 }} Accessed 6. March 2010.</ref> She is the second African-American, first Asian-American and second woman elected to Tacoma\u2019s highest office.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.governing.com/gov-institute/wig/wig-marilyn-strickland.html/ |title=Governing Institute, 2015 \"Women in Government Leadership Program\" honoree |access-date=2016-07-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160513113046/http://www.governing.com/gov-institute/wig/wig-marilyn-strickland.html |archive-date=2016-05-13 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\nDuring her eight years in office, Strickland was active in the [[U.S. Conference of Mayors]] and brought national attention to Tacoma.<ref>{{cite news |last=Ruud |first=Candice |date=December 29, 2017 |title='We've had a good run,' says Marilyn Strickland as she departs the Mayor's Office |url=http://www.thenewstribune.com/news/politics-government/article192211314.html |work=The News Tribune |accessdate=January 2, 2018}}</ref>\n\nAfter leaving office as Mayor of Tacoma, she became president and chief executive of the Seattle Metropolitan Chamber of Commerce.<ref>{{cite news | last=James | first=Will | date=January 20, 2018 | title=Seattle, meet your new Chamber Of Commerce presidential from Tacoma | url=http://knkx.org/post/seattle-meet-your-new-chamber-commerce-president-tacoma | work=KNKX Radio | accessdate=January 21, 2018}}</ref>\n\nFormer Mayor Strickland announced in December 2019 that she is running in the 2020 Democratic primary for Washington state's Tenth Congressional district seat, replacing incumbent Denny Heck who had announced his retirement earlier in 2019. <ref>{{cite news | last=Drew | first=James | date=December 19, 2019 | title=Former Tacoma mayor Marilyn Strickland declares for Congress | url=https://www.thenewstribune.com/news/politics-government/article238551413.html | work= Tacoma News Tribune| accessdate=January 1, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Ethics violation investigation ==\n\nIn May 2010 the Tacoma Board of Ethics sanctioned Mayor Marilyn Strickland for accepting [[frequent flyer miles]] from a local businessman for an official trip to Asia. Mayor Strickland accepted the sanction and returned the value of the frequent flyer miles to the businessman.<ref>[https://archive.is/20120715223304/http://seattletimes.nwsource.com/html/localnews/2015104931_apwatacomamayorethics.html \"Tacoma Board of Ethics says mayor violated code\"]</ref>\n\n== References ==\n<references />\n\n== Links ==\n\n[http://www.facebook.com/pages/Marilyn-Strickland/58702593554  Marilyn Strickland on Facebook]\n\nhttps://www.stricklandforwashington.com\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Strickland, Marilyn}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1962 births]]\n[[Category:African-American mayors]]\n[[Category:African-American people in Washington (state) politics]]\n[[Category:African-American women in politics]]\n[[Category:Women mayors of places in Washington (state)]]\n[[Category:Mayors of Tacoma, Washington]]\n[[Category:21st-century American politicians]]\n[[Category:21st-century American women politicians]]\n[[Category:Washington (state) Democrats]]\n\n{{Washington-mayor-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Mayor\n| name        = Marilyn Strickland\n| image       = Marilyn Strickland (18655920073).jpg \n| caption     = \n| office      = Mayor of [[Tacoma, Washington]]\n| term_start  = January 5, 2010\n| term_end    = January 2, 2018\n| predecessor = [[Bill Baarsma]]\n| successor   = [[Victoria Woodards]]\n| birth_date  = {{birth year and age|1962}}\n| birth_place = [[Seoul]], [[South Korea]]\n| state2      = \n| term_start2 = \n| term_end2   = \n| preceded2   = \n| succeeded2  = \n| death_date  = \n| death_place = \n| party       = [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]\n| spouse      = \n| relations   = \n| children    = \n| residence   = \n| alma_mater  = [[Clark Atlanta University]] <small>([[Masters of Business Administration|M.B.A.]])</small><br/>[[University of Washington]] <small>([[Bachelor of Arts|B.A.]])\n| occupation  = \n| profession  = \n| religion    = \n| signature   = \n| website     = \n| footnotes   = \n}}\n\n'''Marilyn Strickland''' (born 1962) is an [[Politics of the United States|American politician]] and former [[Mayor]] of the City of [[Tacoma, Washington]].\n\n== Biography ==\n\nMarylin Strickland was born in [[Seoul]], [[South Korea]] where her father was [[USFK|stationed]]. In 1967 her father was assigned to  [[Fort Lewis]], Washington, and the family moved to Tacoma.\n\nStrickland has worked as a marketing manager for [[Starbucks]] and as an officer in the Tacoma Public Library System. She is a graduate of the [[University of Washington]] and holds a [[Master\u2019s Degree]] in [[Business Administration]] from [[Clark-Atlanta University]].<ref>[http://www.cityoftacoma.org/page.aspx?nid=54#Strickland ''City of Tacoma] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080329124255/http://www.cityoftacoma.org/Page.aspx?nid=54 |date=2008-03-29 }} Accessed 25 October 2012</ref>\n\nShe was elected in 2008 for the [[Tacoma City Council]].<ref>[http://themelononline.com/2009/04/interview-with-marilyn-strickland-tacoma-mayoral-candidate/  ''The Melon Interview with Marylin Strickland''] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090430155719/http://themelononline.com/2009/04/interview-with-marilyn-strickland-tacoma-mayoral-candidate/ |date=2009-04-30 }} Accessed 6. March 2010.</ref> She is the second African-American, first Asian-American and second woman elected to Tacoma\u2019s highest office.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.governing.com/gov-institute/wig/wig-marilyn-strickland.html/ |title=Governing Institute, 2015 \"Women in Government Leadership Program\" honoree |access-date=2016-07-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160513113046/http://www.governing.com/gov-institute/wig/wig-marilyn-strickland.html |archive-date=2016-05-13 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\nDuring her eight years in office, Strickland was active in the [[U.S. Conference of Mayors]] and brought national attention to Tacoma.<ref>{{cite news |last=Ruud |first=Candice |date=December 29, 2017 |title='We've had a good run,' says Marilyn Strickland as she departs the Mayor's Office |url=http://www.thenewstribune.com/news/politics-government/article192211314.html |work=The News Tribune |accessdate=January 2, 2018}}</ref>\n\nAfter leaving office as Mayor of Tacoma, she became president and chief executive of the Seattle Metropolitan Chamber of Commerce.<ref>{{cite news | last=James | first=Will | date=January 20, 2018 | title=Seattle, meet your new Chamber Of Commerce presidential from Tacoma | url=http://knkx.org/post/seattle-meet-your-new-chamber-commerce-president-tacoma | work=KNKX Radio | accessdate=January 21, 2018}}</ref>\n\nFormer Mayor Strickland announced in December 2019 that she is running in the 2020 Democratic primary for Washington state's Tenth Congressional district seat, replacing incumbent Denny Heck who had announced his retirement earlier in 2019. <ref>{{cite news | last=Drew | first=James | date=December 19, 2019 | title=Former Tacoma mayor Marilyn Strickland declares for Congress | url=https://www.thenewstribune.com/news/politics-government/article238551413.html | work= Tacoma News Tribune| accessdate=January 1, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Ethics violation investigation ==\n\nIn May 2010 the Tacoma Board of Ethics sanctioned Mayor Marilyn Strickland for accepting [[frequent flyer miles]] from a local businessman for an official trip to Asia. Mayor Strickland accepted the sanction and returned the value of the frequent flyer miles to the businessman.<ref>[https://archive.is/20120715223304/http://seattletimes.nwsource.com/html/localnews/2015104931_apwatacomamayorethics.html \"Tacoma Board of Ethics says mayor violated code\"]</ref>\n\n== References ==\n<references />\n\n== Links ==\n\n[http://www.facebook.com/pages/Marilyn-Strickland/58702593554  Marilyn Strickland on Facebook]\n\nhttps://www.stricklandforwashington.com\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Strickland, Marilyn}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1962 births]]\n[[Category:African-American mayors]]\n[[Category:African-American people in Washington (state) politics]]\n[[Category:African-American women in politics]]\n[[Category:Women mayors of places in Washington (state)]]\n[[Category:Mayors of Tacoma, Washington]]\n[[Category:21st-century American politicians]]\n[[Category:21st-century American women politicians]]\n[[Category:Washington (state) Democrats]]\n\n{{Washington-mayor-stub}}\n", "name_user": "EdmundT", "label": "safe", "comment": "Spelling", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Marilyn_Strickland"}
{"title_page": "NYSE Euronext", "text_new": "{{more citations needed|date=January 2013}}\n{{Infobox company\n|name = NYSE Euronext, Inc.\n|logo = [[File:NYSE Euronext 2012 logo.svg|200px|The NYSE Euronext logo as of 2012.]]\n|type = Subsidiary\n|predecessors = NYSE Group, Inc.<br />Euronext N.V.\n|industry = [[Financial services]]\n|foundation = {{Start date|2007|04|4}}\n|defunct = 2013\n|location_city = [[Wall Street|11 Wall Street]], [[New York City|New York]], [[New York (state)]]\n|location_country = [[United States]]  \n|area_served = United States, European Union\n|fate = Acquired by [[Intercontinental Exchange]], [[Euronext]] later spun off\n|key_people = [[Duncan L. Niederauer]]<br>(CEO) \n|services = [[Derivative (finance)|Derivatives]], [[equity trading]] platforms, [[Futures contract|futures]] and [[Option (finance)|options]] [[Financial market|markets]], [[market data]], [[Stock exchange|securities exchanges]]\n|revenue = US$ 3.75 billion (2013)<ref name=\"AR2010\">{{cite web |url=https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1368007/000136800713000005/nyx-20121231x10k.htm/item=UGFyZW50SUQ9MzU2NjUzM3xDaGlsZElEPTQxMjc4MHxUeXBlPTI=&t=1|title=Annual Results 2010|publisher=NYSE Euronext|accessdate=27 February 2011}}</ref>\n|operating_income = US$ {{0|0}}850&nbsp;million (2011)<ref name=\"AR2010\"/>\n|net_income = US$ {{0|0}}619&nbsp;million (2011)<ref name=\"AR2010\"/>\n|assets = US$ 13.07&nbsp;billion (2011)<ref name=\"AR2010\"/>\n|equity = US$ 6.581&nbsp;billion (2011)<ref name=\"AR2010\"/>\n|num_employees = 3,061 (2012)<ref name=\"AR2010\"/>\n|divisions = [[New York Stock Exchange]],<br />[[Euronext]] ([[Euronext Amsterdam|Amsterdam]], [[Euronext Paris|Paris]], [[Euronext Brussels|Brussels]], [[Euronext Lisbon|Lisbon]]),<br />[[NYSE Arca]], [[Euronext.liffe|NYSE Liffe]], [[NYSE Technologies]]\n|parent = [[Intercontinental Exchange]]\n|homepage = {{URL|http://www.nyx.com|NYX.com}}\n}}\n\n'''NYSE Euronext, Inc.''' was a Euro-American [[Multinational corporation|multinational]] [[financial services]] corporation that operated multiple [[Stock exchange|securities exchanges]], including the [[New York Stock Exchange]], [[Euronext]] and [[NYSE Arca]] (formerly known as ArcaEx). NYSE merged with Archipelago Holdings on March 7, 2006, forming NYSE Group, Inc.<ref>{{cite web|title=\"Archipelago\" refers to, prior to and following the completion of its merger with the New York Stock Exchange, Inc., which occurred on March 7, 2006, Archipelago Holdings, Inc., a Delaware corporation, and, where the context requires, its predecessor, Archipelago Holdings, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company;|url=https://www.nyse.com/pdfs/10Q_08.PDF|publisher=NYSE|access-date=2017-09-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130526202707/http://www.nyse.com/pdfs/10Q_08.PDF|archive-date=2013-05-26|url-status=dead}}</ref> On April 4, 2007, NYSE Group, Inc. merged with Euronext N.V. to form the first global equities exchange, with its headquarters in [[Lower Manhattan]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.businessweek.com/ap/financialnews/D9LDDVSO1.htm |title=NYSE, Deutsche Boerse are already global companies|author=Pallavi Gogoi|date=February 15, 2011<!--, 3:20PM ET -->|publisher=[[Bloomberg Businessweek]]|accessdate=February 5, 2012}}</ref> The corporation was then acquired by [[Intercontinental Exchange]], which subsequently spun off Euronext.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://dealbook.nytimes.com/2014/05/27/intercontinentalexchange-announces-plans-to-float-euronext/|title=IntercontinentalExchange Set to Spin Off Euronext|author=Chad Bray|date=May 27, 2014|work=[[New York Times]]|accessdate=August 25, 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Overview==\nNYSE Euronext offers a broad and growing array of financial products and services in cash equities, [[futures contract|futures]], [[option (finance)|option]]s, [[exchange-traded product]]s (ETPs), [[bond (finance)|bond]]s, market data, and commercial technology. Spanning multiple asset classes and six countries, the company's exchanges include the New York Stock Exchange, Liffe, Euronext and NYSE Arca.  With more than 8,000<ref>{{cite web|title=With approximately 8,000 listed issues (excluding European Structured Products), NYSE Euronext's equities markets \u2013 the New York Stock Exchange, NYSE Euronext, NYSE Amex, NYSE Alternext and NYSE Arca \u2013 represent one-third of the world's equities trading, the most liquidity of any global exchange group|url=https://www.nyse.com/press/1310637000012.html|access-date=2017-09-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140217042551/http://www.nyse.com/press/1310637000012.html|archive-date=2014-02-17|url-status=dead}}</ref> listed issues (which includes 90% of the [[Dow Jones Industrial Average]] and 80% of the [[S&P 500]],<ref>{{cite web|title=19.90% of the Dow Jones Industrial Average; 80% of the S&P 500|url=https://www.nyse.com/exccelerate/community/company-you-keep.html|access-date=2017-09-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130526200048/http://www.nyse.com/exccelerate/community/company-you-keep.html|archive-date=2013-05-26|url-status=dead}}</ref> trading on NYSE Euronext's equity markets represents more than one-third of the world's cash equities volume. The company also manages the leading European derivatives exchange by value of trading.\n\nNYSE Euronext is part of the S&P 500 index and the only exchange operator in the [[S&P 100|S&P 100 index]].<ref>{{cite web|title=NYSE Euronext is in the S&P 500 index, and is the only exchange operator in the S&P 100 index and Fortune 500.|url=http://www.nyseblue.com/news/pr-NYSE-Euronext-and-APX-Complete-Transaction-and-form-NYSE-Blue.htm|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120226170212/http://www.nyseblue.com/news/pr-NYSE-Euronext-and-APX-Complete-Transaction-and-form-NYSE-Blue.htm|archivedate=2012-02-26}}</ref>\n\nNYSE Euronext is a [[Delaware]] corporation, though the principal executive office of NYSE Euronext is located at 11 Wall Street, New York, New York 10005. The European headquarters are at 39 Rue Cambon, 75001 in [[Paris]], [[France]].\n\n==Locations==\nBelow is a list of major NYSE Euronext locations:\n* [[Amsterdam]], [[Netherlands]]\n* [[Belfast]], [[Northern Ireland]]\n* [[Brussels]], [[Belgium]]\n* [[Chicago]], [[Illinois]], [[United States of America]]\n* [[Lisbon]], [[Portugal]]\n* [[London]], [[United Kingdom]]\n* [[New York City]], [[New York State|New York]], [[United States of America]]\n* [[Palo Alto]], [[California]], [[United States of America]]\n* [[Paris]], [[France]]\n* [[San Francisco]], [[California]], [[United States of America]]\n\n==Mergers and acquisitions==\n\n===NYSE and Archipelago Holdings===\n[https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2005/12/06/AR2005120601744.html The merger between NYSE and Archipelago Holdings] was initially approved in 2005 by a 95% majority of voting NYSE members.<ref>{{cite news|title=About 90 percent of the Big Board's 1,366 members voted, and 95 percent of those voted in favor of the merger.|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2005/12/06/AR2005120601744.html | work=The Washington Post | first1=Dean|last1=Starkman|first2=Ben|last2=White|date=December 7, 2005}}</ref> The acquisition of Archipelago, which held possession of highly regarded market technology at the time, was intended to bring automated trading to NYSE markets (which had previously utilized an \"[[open outcry]]\" system) and increase efficiency.\n\nFor the first time in its 213-year history, the New York Stock Exchange became a for-profit company, and began trading publicly on its own stock exchange under the NYX ticker.<ref>{{cite news|title=The New York Stock Exchange voted to acquire a Chicago-based electronic stock-exchange company, Archipelago Holdings Inc., in a historic step that will transform the 213-year-old Big Board from a tradition-bound concern owned by and for its members to a profit-seeking, publicly traded company expected to compete in the evolving world of electronic markets.|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2005/12/06/AR2005120601744.html | work=The Washington Post | first1=Dean|last1=Starkman|first2=Ben|last2=White|date=December 7, 2005}}</ref> Owners of the 1,366 NYSE seats received 80,177 shares of NYSE Group stock plus $300,000 in cash and $70,571 in dividends for each seat.<ref>{{cite web|title=Under the final agreement, owners of the 1,366 seats on the NYSE received 80,177 shares of NYSE Group stock plus $300,000 in cash and another $70,571 in dividends.|url=http://www.nbcnews.com/id/11725095}}</ref> The completion of this deal created two new branches of the NYSE Group: NYSE Arca and NYSE Arca Europe, which launched after the acquisition of Euronext.\n\n===NYSE Group and Euronext merger April 4, 2007===\n[[File:Logo of NYSE Euronext 2007-2012.svg|thumb|Logo used between 2007 and 2012]]\nIn April 2006, NYSE Group and Euronext signed a merger agreement, subject to shareholder vote and regulatory approval.<ref>{{cite web|title=On April 3, 2007, NYSE Group and Euronext completed their historical business combination to create NYSE Euronext, the world's leading and most liquid exchange group.|url=https://www.nyse.com/about/newsevents/1175510198386}}{{Dead link|date=September 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> Euronext shareholders gave approval to the transaction on December 19, 2006, and shareholders from the NYSE Group followed suit one day later.<ref>{{cite web |title=Approximately 99.7 percent of NYSE Group, Inc. (NYSE: NYX) shareholders who voted have approved the Exchange's proposed combination with Euronext N.V., whose shareholders yesterday approved this historic transaction that creates the first truly global exchange group. |url=https://www.nyse.com/press/1166613560168.html |date=December 20, 2006 <!-- |accessdate=February 2013 --> |series=Press Release |publisher=New York Stock Exchange (NYSE) |access-date=2017-09-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130526210020/http://www.nyse.com/press/1166613560168.html |archive-date=2013-05-26 |url-status=dead }}</ref> In April 2007 the Euronext shareholders tendering shares can receive NYSE shares and cash amounting to $11,141 million from NYSE Euronext for their assets.<ref>{{cite web |title=NYSEGgroup and EURONEXT N.V. agree to a merger of Equals. Combination Will Create The First Global Exchange; Joint Press/Analyst Conference Scheduled in Paris, Friday, June 2, 2006. |url=http://www1.nyse.com/press/1149157439121.html |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130625020945/http://www.nyse.com/press/1149157439121.html |archivedate=June 25, 2013 }}</ref> About 94% of the 112,557,259 shares are tendered in the first round.<ref>Euronext N.V. Annual report for the year 2007</ref>\n\nThe NYSE Group and Euronext merger on April 4, 2007, signaled the creation of the world's largest and most [[Liquidity|liquid]] exchange group\u2014NYSE Euronext.<ref name=NYSE20070405>{{cite web |title=NYSE Euronext (NYSE/New York and Euronext/Paris: NYX) and offers the most diverse array of financial products and services. |url=https://www.nyse.com/about/newsevents/1149243292355.html |date=April 5, 2007<!-- |accessdate=February 2013 --> |series=Press Release |publisher=New York Stock Exchange (NYSE) |access-date=2017-09-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110319022431/http://www.nyse.com/about/newsevents/1149243292355.html |archive-date=2011-03-19 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n===NYSE Euronext and NYFIX===\nNYSE Euronext, through its wholly owned subsidiary NYSE Technologies, Inc. acquired  NYFIX, Inc. (Nasdaq: NYFX) for $144 million in November 2009. NYSE Euronext incorporated NYFIX's trading software into the company's package of offerings to customers.<ref name=NYSE20090827>{{cite web |location=New York |date=August 27, 2009 |url=https://www.nyse.com/press/1251367635488.html |title=NYSE Euronext's acquisition of NYFIX <!-- |accessdate=February 2013 --> |access-date=2017-09-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130526202023/http://www.nyse.com/press/1251367635488.html |archive-date=2013-05-26 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n===Attempted merger between NYSE Euronext and Deutsche B\u00f6rse===\nIn 2011, ''[[Bloomberg L.P.|Bloomberg]]'' reported that the German exchange operator [[Deutsche B\u00f6rse]] was in advanced talks to buy NYSE Euronext for $9.53 billion in a deal that would create the world's largest trading powerhouse.<ref>{{cite web|title=Deutsche Boerse AG's $9.53 billion all-stock purchase of New York Stock Exchange parent NYSE Euronext creates the world's largest owner of equities and derivatives markets, and may spur additional mergers.|url=http://www.businessweek.com/news/2011-02-15/deutsche-boerse-9-53-billion-nyse-buy-may-spur-deals}}</ref> The shares of both companies were temporarily frozen on the news due to the risk of large price movements and clarifications of the deal. A successful deal would see the new company becoming the world's largest stock exchange operator with a market capitalization of listed companies equal to $15 trillion.<ref>{{cite web|title=While the merged entity will list corporations with about $15 trillion in value, more than any other exchange, what may prove more lucrative is ownership of growing venues for trading futures and options, said Rich Repetto, a New York-based analyst at Sandler O'Neill & Partners LP.|url=http://www.businessweek.com/news/2011-02-15/deutsche-boerse-9-53-billion-nyse-buy-may-spur-deals}}</ref>\n\nThe proposed group would have dual headquarters, in Deutsche Boerse's newly built green tower near [[Frankfurt]], [[Germany]], and in New York City at 11 Wall Street. It would be led by a board with seventeen members\u2014fifteen directors plus the Chairman and the CEO. Of the fifteen directors, nine to be designated by Deutsche Boerse and six by NYSE Euronext. Current NYSE Euronext CEO Duncan Niederauer would assume the same role with the newly founded company and would lead an Executive Committee with an equal number of current Deutsche Boerse and NYSE Euronext executives.<ref>{{cite web|title=The group will have dual headquarters, in Deutsche Boerse's newly built green tower near Frankfurt and in New York, at 11 Wall Street, home to the iconic New York Stock Exchange trading floor, and would take advantage of its existing global operations. The Company would be led by a one-tier board with 17 members \u2013 15 directors plus the Chairman and the CEO. Of the fifteen directors, nine would be designated by Deutsche Boerse and six by NYSE Euronext. Reto Francioni would be Chairman, and would also be responsible for group strategy and global relationship management. Duncan Niederauer would be Chief Executive Officer and would lead an Executive Committee with an equal number of current Deutsche Boerse and NYSE Euronext executives.|url=http://ir.nyse.com/phoenix.zhtml?c=129145&p=irol-newsArticle&ID=1529114}}</ref>\n\nOn July 7, 2011, NYSE Euronext shareholders voted in favor of the merger, and on July 13, 2011, Deutsche Boerse shareholders approved the deal as well. These decisions move the two sides closer to completing the transaction, which must still pass through forty separate regulatory approval processes to be finalized.<ref>{{cite news|title=Deutsche Boerse AG (DB1.XE) on Thursday secured shareholder backing for its planned merger with NYSE Euronext (NYX), focusing attention on efforts to win regulatory clearance for what would be the world's largest exchange operator. Investors in both companies placed faith in the ability of exchange executives to shepherd the combination through a gauntlet of more than 40 separate regulatory approval processes \u2013 including a lengthy review by the European Union \u2013 without ceding too many concessions that might dilute is planned benefits. |url=https://online.wsj.com/article/BT-CO-20110714-710899.html }}{{dead link|date=June 2016|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref>\n\nThe merger was subject to review in both the United States and with the European Union (EU) for concerns it could create a \u201c[[de facto monopoly|''de facto'' monopoly]]\u201d.\n \nIn October 2011, CEO Niederauer said the company had received the EU's so-called statement of objections, which was more than 100 pages long, and would be responding within two weeks, possibly by asking for the opportunity for an oral hearing with the regulators. The EU examination of the proposal formally began June 29 has said its expanded probe has a Dec. 13 deadline. In March, [[Joaquin Almunia]], the EU's antitrust commissioner, expressed concern that the deal would maybe monopolize the derivatives market due to Deutsche Boerse's \u201cvertical silo\u201d which routes all trade clearing through its own services. Almunia said then he preferred a \u201cmore open business model\u201d for markets.<ref>Rummer, Andrew, and Peter Chapman, editors, [http://news.businessweek.com/article.asp?documentKey=1376-LSYAH56K50Y601-09845DBNU4QT522C0IPVDS93NA \"NYSE Euronext May Seek EU Hearing to Defend Deutsche Boerse Deal\"]{{dead link|date=December 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}, ''Bloomberg'', October 13, 2011 11:06 am EDT. Retrieved 2011-10-13.</ref>\n\nOn December 22, 2011, Deutsche Boerse won U.S. antitrust approval to buy NYSE Euronext, on condition that a Deutsche Boerse subsidiary, the International Securities Exchange, divest its 31.5 percent interest in [[Direct Edge]].<ref>[https://www.reuters.com/article/2011/12/22/us-nyse-deutscheboerse-idUSTRE7BL1CE20111222 Deutsche Boerse (DB1Gn.DE) won U.S. antitrust approval to buy NYSE Euronext (NYX.N) in a $9 billion deal to create the world's No. 1 exchange operator, but the transaction still faces serious regulatory headwinds in Europe.] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150914053146/https://www.reuters.com/article/2011/12/22/us-nyse-deutscheboerse-idUSTRE7BL1CE20111222 |date=September 14, 2015 }}, ''Reuters'', Dec 22, 2011. Retrieved 09-01-2012.</ref> NYSE Euronext and Deutsche Boerse AG delayed the deadline for completing their merger until March 31, 2012 so the exchange operators could try to persuade European regulators to approve the deal.<ref>[https://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-27/nyse-euronext-deutsche-boerse-merger-date-extended-to-march-31.html NYSE, Deutsche Boerse Merger Date Extended] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131103085042/http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-27/nyse-euronext-deutsche-boerse-merger-date-extended-to-march-31.html |date=November 3, 2013 }}, ''Bloomberg'', Dec 28, 2011. Retrieved 09-01-2012.</ref>\n\nOn February 1, 2012, the European Union blocked the planned merger between NYSE Euronext and Deutsche Boerse. The European Commission\u2014the EU's executive body\u2014ruled against the merger because, they said, the combined exchange would control more than 90% of the trade in European derivatives. The European Commission report stated, \"The merger between Deutsche Boerse and NYSE Euronext would have led to a near-monopoly in European financial derivatives worldwide... These markets are at the heart of the financial system and it is crucial for the whole European economy that they remain competitive\".<ref>[https://www.npr.org/2012/02/01/146215168/, EU blocks Deutsche Boerse NYSE Euronext merger]{{dead link|date=December 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}, ''The Associated Press'', Feb 1, 2012. Retrieved 2012-02-01.</ref>\n\nOn February 2, 2012, the NYSE Euronext and Deutsche B\u00f6rse agreed with strong opposition by the EU for the planned merger, to scrap the merger.<ref>[https://www.nyse.com/press/1328178461772.html NYSE Euronext Press Release] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150712071646/http://www.nyse.com/press/1328178461772.html |date=July 12, 2015 }}</ref>\n\n===Intercontinental Exchange acquisition of NYSE Euronext===\nOn December 20, 2012, the boards of directors of both [[Intercontinental Exchange]] (ICE) and the NYSE Euronext approved an $8 billion acquisition of NYSE Euronext. Under the terms shareholders of NYSE would receive either $33.12 in cash for each share or .2581 IntercontinentalExchange Inc. shares, or a combination of $11.27 in cash per share plus .1703 shares of stock.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.cbsnews.com/8301-505123_162-57560197/intercontinentalexchange-to-buy-nyse-for-$8.2b/ |via=[[CBS News]] |publisher=[[Associated Press]] |title=IntercontinentalExchange to buy NYSE for $8.2B |date=December 20, 2012 |accessdate=August 25, 2014}}</ref> The acquisition is subject to regulator approval, though since the operations of ICE and NYSE have little in common\u2014ICE is largely devoted to trading commodities, as opposed to NYSE's business of trading stocks and securities\u2014the deal is not expected to be blocked.<ref name=\"nytimes\">{{cite news | url=https://dealbook.nytimes.com/2012/12/20/upstart-market-operator-clinches-8-2-billion-deal-for-n-y-s-e/?hp | title=Upstart Market Operator Clinches $8.2 Billion Deal for N.Y.S.E. | work=The New York Times | date=December 20, 2012 | accessdate=December 20, 2012}}</ref> ICE said that after the deal closed it would sell the Euronext portion of the company, including stock exchanges in Amsterdam, Brussels, Lisbon and Paris.<ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-20802445 | title=NYSE agrees to be sold to rival ICE for $8bn | publisher=BBC News Online | date=December 20, 2012 | accessdate=December 20, 2012}}</ref>  The deal went through and Euronext is a sister division to NYSE and part of ICE. ICE CEO [[Jeffrey C. Sprecher]] would continue in that position at the combined company, while NYSE CEO Duncan Niederauer would serve as president.<ref name=\"nytimes\"/>  The future of the New York Stock Exchange's historic trading floor under ICE has not been announced.  ICE closed the high profile and historic trading floors of its other earlier acquisitions\u2014the [[International Petroleum Exchange]] and the [[New York Board of Trade]] in New York.<ref name=\"nytimes1\">{{cite news| url=https://www.nytimes.com/2013/01/20/business/jeffrey-sprechers-improbable-path-to-buying-the-nyse.html?partner=rss&emc=rss&pagewanted=print | work=The New York Times | first=Nathaniel | last=Popper | title=Jeffrey Sprecher's Improbable Path to Buying the N.Y.S.E | date=January 19, 2013}}</ref>\n\n==Company structure==\n===Derivatives===\nThe Derivatives segment consists of NYSE Euronext's derivatives trading and clearing businesses. This includes [[NYSE Liffe]], NYSE Liffe Clearing, NYSE Liffe US, [[NYSE Amex]] Options, NYSE Arca Option, and related derivatives market data.<ref name=\"annual report\">{{cite web|title=NYSE Euronext annual report|url=http://phx.corporate-ir.net/External.File?item=UGFyZW50SUQ9ODU5NzN8Q2hpbGRJRD0tMXxUeXBlPTM=&t=1}}</ref>\n\n====NYSE Liffe====\nNYSE Liffe comprises the derivatives market operated by LIFFE Administration and Management, Euronext Amsterdam, Euronext Brussels, Euronext Lisbon, and Euronext Paris. It offers customers the advantages of one of the most technologically advanced derivatives trading platforms as well as one of the widest choices of products of any derivatives market.<ref name=\"annual report\"/>\n\nThrough a single [[electronic trading platform]], NYSE Liffe offers customers access to a wide range of [[Interest rate|interest-rate]], [[Equity (finance)|equity]], [[Stock market index|index]], [[commodity]] and currency derivative products. This platform has been designed to handle significant order flows and transaction volumes. Orders can be matched either on a price/time or pro rata basis, configurable by contract, with transacted prices and volumes and the aggregate size of all bids and offers at each price level updated on a real-time basis. Users can continually notified of all active orders in the central order book, making market depth easy to monitor.<ref name=\"annual report\"/>\n\nNYSE Liffe also offers its customers the Bclear and Cscreen services, which bridge the listed and [[Over-the-counter (finance)|over-the-counter]] (OTC) markets. This provides a simple and cost-effective way to register and process wholesale derivatives trades through NYSE Liffe to clearing at NYSE Liffe Clearing. Following the launch of NYSE Liffe Clearing, NYSE Liffe assumed full responsibility for clearing activities on its own London market.<ref name=\"annual report\"/>\n\nNYSE Liffe US, NYSE Euronext's U.S. futures exchange, makes available for trading full- and mini-sized gold and silver futures, options on full-sized gold and silver futures and futures on [[Morgan Stanley Capital International]] (MSCI) Indices. A significant minority equity stake in NYSE Liffe US is held by six external investors: [[Citadel|Citadel Securities]], DRW Investments, [[Global Electronic Trading Company|Getco]], [[Goldman Sachs]], [[Morgan Stanley]] and [[UBS]]. Under this ownership structure, NYSE Euronext remains the largest shareholder in the entity and consolidates its financial reporting. NYSE Euronext manages the day-to-day operations of NYSE Liffe US, which operates under the supervision of a separate board of directors.<ref name=\"annual report\"/>\n\n====NYSE Amex Options====\nThe NYSE Amex Options business uses a hybrid model combining both auction-based and electronic trading capabilities that is designed to provide a stable, liquid and less volatile market. This feature provides the opportunity for price and/or size improvement.<ref name=\"annual report\"/>\n\nIn 2010, NYSE Euronext announced the sale of a significant equity interest in NYSE Amex Options to seven external investors: [[Bank of America Merrill Lynch]], [[Barclays Capital]], Citadel Securities, [[Citi]], Goldman Sachs, [[TD Ameritrade]], and UBS. Under the framework, NYSE Euronext remains the largest shareholder in the entity and manages the day-to-day operations of NYSE Amex Options, which operates under the supervision of a separate board of directors and chief executive officer. NYSE Euronext consolidates this entity for financial reporting purposes.<ref name=\"annual report\"/>\n\n====NYSE Arca Options====\nNYSE Arca Options, the other of NYSE Euronext's two U.S. options exchanges, offers immediate, cost-effective electronic order execution in nearly two thousand options issues. The NYSE Arca Options business uses a technology platform and market structure designed to enhance the speed and quality of trade execution for its customers, as well as to attract additional sources of liquidity. Its structure allows market makers to access its markets remotely and integrates floor-based participants as well.<ref name=\"annual report\"/>\n\n===Cash Trading and Listings===\nThe Cash Trading and Listings segment includes the New York Stock Exchange, Euronext, NYSE Amex, NYSE Arca, NYSE Alternext, NYSE Arca Europe, SmartPool, [[BlueNext]], and NYSE Blue, as well as related cash trading market data.<ref name=\"annual report\"/>\n\n====New York Stock Exchange====\nThe [[New York Stock Exchange]] is registered as a national securities exchange under the [[Exchange Act]]. In addition to common stock, preferred stock and [[warrant (finance)|warrants]], the NYSE lists debt and corporate structured products, such as capital securities, mandatory convertibles, and repackaged securities.<ref name=\"annual report\"/>\n\n====Euronext====\n[[Euronext]] is the first integrated cross-border exchange, combining the stock exchanges of Amsterdam, Paris, Brussels and Lisbon into a single market. Issuers who meet [[European Union]] regulatory standards are qualified for listing on the regulated markets operated by Euronext. The company's exchanges list a wide variety of securities, including domestic and international equity securities, convertible bonds, warrants, trackers and debt securities, including corporate and government bonds.<ref name=\"annual report\"/>\n\nAll of Euronext's markets are operated by its subsidiaries, each of which holds a national license as an exchange operator.<ref name=\"annual report\"/>\n\n====NYSE Amex====\nNYSE Euronext completed its acquisition of the [[American Stock Exchange|Amex]] (American Stock Exchange) on October 1, 2008. The transaction extended NYSE Euronext's leadership in U.S. option, cash equities, and [[exchange-traded fund]]s (ETFs), making it the third largest U.S. equity options marketplace based on number of contracts traded. Since the merger, Amex has been integrated into the company, with former Amex listings now trading directly on the NYSE, and has begun trading certain [[Nasdaq]]-listed securities.<ref name=\"annual report\"/>\n\nNYSE Arca is the first electronic market to offer listed ETP issuers a Lead Market Maker program, which encourages liquidity provision that contributes to the best prices and depth in the ETP marketplace. It is registered as a national securities exchange under the Exchange Act.<ref name=\"annual report\"/>\n\n====NYSE Alternext====\n\n[[NYSE Alternext]] was created by NYSE Euronext to meet the needs of small and mid-sized companies seeking simplified access to the stock market. Its streamlined listing requirements and trading rules are suited to the size and business needs of such firms. The rules also ensure investor transparency. NYSE Alternext's special listing procedures, unique market model, and listings of sponsor companies for members are its most notable features.<ref name=\"annual report\"/>\n\nNYSE Alternext is an exchange-regulated market with a lighter regulatory regime. It is not a regulated market as defined by the [[Markets in Financial Instruments Directive]] (MiFID), but rather is regulated by NYSE Euronext through a body of rules applicable to intermediaries and listed companies.<ref name=\"annual report\"/>\n\n====NYSE Arca Europe====\nNYSE Arca Europe is a pan-European [[multilateral trading facility]] (MTF) that extends the trading scope of Euronext's regulated markets by adding [[Blue chip (stock market)|blue-chip]] stocks from 14 European countries: [[Austria]], [[Czech Republic]], [[Denmark]], [[Finland]], [[France]], [[Germany]], [[Hungary]], [[Ireland]], [[Italy]], [[Norway]], [[Spain]], [[Sweden]], [[Switzerland]], and the United Kingdom. Arca Europe integrates this trading facility with the other business components of the company, giving customers the flexibility in trading of an MTF while maintaining the global market reach of NYSE Euronext.<ref name=\"annual report\"/>\n\n====SmartPool====\n[https://web.archive.org/web/20120426060115/http://www.tradeonsmartpool.com/ SmartPool Trading Limited] is a UK-registered company supplying an MTF approved by the [[Financial Services Authority]] (FSA). It provides an exchange-led dark pool for the execution of block orders covering 15 different European markets, with a full central counter party back-end through [[LCH.Clearnet]] and EuroCCP. SmartPool was created by NYSE Euronext in partnership with [[BNP Paribas]], [[HSBC]], and [[J.P. Morgan Chase]].<ref name=\"annual report\"/>\n\n====BlueNext and NYSE Blue====\nNYSE Euronext holds a 60% interest in [[BlueNext]] with the remaining 40% held by CDC Climat. BlueNext operates a spot market in carbon dioxide emission allowances and credits that is the European leader in the field. It seeks to establish a leading position in trading in environment-related instruments, and has also launched a futures market with physical delivery of allowances and credits.<ref name=\"annual report\"/>\n\nIn September 2010, NYSE Euronext announced plans to create NYSE Blue, a new global company that will focus on environmental and sustainable energy markets. NYSE Euronext contributed its ownership in BlueNext in return for a majority interest in NYSE Blue, and [[APX|APX, Inc.]] (a leading provider of regulatory infrastructure and services for environmental and sustainable energy markets) will contribute its business in return for a minority interest in the venture. The transaction closed on February 18, 2011.<ref name=\"annual report\"/>\n\n===Information Services and Technology Solutions===\n\nThe Information Services and Technology Solutions segment refers to NYSE Euronext's commercial technology transactions, data, and infrastructure businesses. NYSE Euronext operates NYSE Technologies, Free Market, and also owns NYFIX, Inc.<ref name=\"annual report\"/>\n\n====NYSE Technologies====\n\n[[NYSE Technologies]] is the commercial technology division of NYSE Euronext.<ref name=\"annual report\"/>\n\nNYSE Technologies operates five business:\n* '''Global Market Data''' offers a broad array of global market information products covering multiple asset classes;\n* '''Trading Solutions''' creates and implements high performance, end-to-end messaging software, real-time market data distribution and integration products;\n* '''Exchange Solutions''' provides multi-asset exchange platform services, managed services and expert consultancy;\n* '''Global Connectivity''' offers one of the world's largest, most reliable financial transaction networks connecting firms and exchanges worldwide;\n* '''Transactions''' primarily comprises the former NYFIX FIX business and incorporates the NYFIX Marketplace and the FIX Software business.\n\n====March\u00e9 Libre====\n\nThe Free Markets of Brussels and Paris, organized by NYSE Euronext, are not regulated markets in the sense of the EU Directive. The criteria for admission to these markets are much simpler, and listing costs are low. They provide a channel for disseminating buy and sell orders, with trades executed by NYSE Euronext member firms. The securities traded on these markets have not gone through any admission procedures and issuers are not subject to any disclosure requirements. The Free Markets serve companies that are too young or too small to be listed on one of the regulated compartments of NYSE Euronext.<ref name=\"annual report\"/>\n\n====NYSE Regulation and FINRA====\nOn May 4, 2010, NYSE Euronext and the [[Financial Industry Regulatory Authority]] (FINRA) announced that FINRA would assume responsibility for performing the [[market surveillance]] and enforcement functions originally conducted by NYSE Regulation. The agreement was subject to review by the [[Securities and Exchange Commission]] (SEC) and was completed in June 2010.<ref name=\"annual report\"/>\n\nUnder the announced agreement, FINRA assumed regulatory functions for NYSE Euronext's U.S. equities and options markets \u2013 the New York Stock Exchange, NYSE Arca, and NYSE Amex. NYSE Euronext, through its subsidiary NYSE Regulation, remains ultimately responsible for overseeing FINRA's performance of regulatory services for the NYSE markets.<ref name=\"annual report\"/>\n\n===Libor administration===\nIn early 2014, NYSE Euronext took over the administration of the [[London interbank offered rate]] from the [[British Bankers Association]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nyse.com/press/1373365567815.html|title=NYSE EURONEXT SUBSIDIARY TO BECOME NEW ADMINISTRATOR OF LIBOR|publisher=NYSE Euronext|date=2013-07-09|accessdate=2013-07-21|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130718141355/http://www.nyse.com/press/1373365567815.html|archivedate=2013-07-18}}</ref> The new administrator is NYSE Euronext Rates Administration Limited,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bba.org.uk/media/article/bba-to-hand-over-administration-of-libor-to-nyse-euronext-rate-administrati|title=BBA to hand over administration of LIBOR to NYSE Euronext Rate Administration Limited|publisher=The British Bankers\u2019 Association|date=2013-07-09|accessdate=2013-07-20|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130713075451/http://www.bba.org.uk/media/article/bba-to-hand-over-administration-of-libor-to-nyse-euronext-rate-administrati|archivedate=2013-07-13}}</ref> a London-based, UK registered company, regulated by the UK\u2019s [[Financial Conduct Authority]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cityam.com/article/libor-now-has-new-administrator-our-reforms-have-gone-much-further|title=Libor now has a new administrator \u2013 but our reforms have gone much further|author=Anthony Browne, chief executive of the British Bankers\u2019 Association|publisher=City A.M.|date=2013-07-11|accessdate=2013-07-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131104030713/http://www.cityam.com/article/libor-now-has-new-administrator-our-reforms-have-gone-much-further|archive-date=2013-11-04|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n==Global marketing and branding==\n\nNYSE Euronext maintains an active marketing campaign, both for its own brand, as well as for its listed companies. The Global Marketing and Branding department is responsible for the full spectrum of NYSE Euronext's brand marketing, including advertising, marketing communications, event management, and market research.<ref>{{cite web|title=As the Global Head of Marketing & Branding for NYSE Euronext, Marisa Ricciardi plays a key role in the strategic development and implementation of the company's branding and communications. Her group is responsible for the full spectrum of NYSE Euronext's brand marketing, including advertising, marketing communications, event management and market research targeting a range of constituents across the globe|url=http://exchanges.nyx.com/marisa-ricciardi/bio|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120607091053/http://exchanges.nyx.com/marisa-ricciardi/bio|archivedate=2012-06-07}}</ref>\n\nThrough the NYSE Global Partnership Program, NYSE Euronext has created a series of strategic resources to support its listed companies' growth initiatives, so as to act as a conduit that enables them to reach new and important audiences.<ref>{{cite web|title=Through the NYSE Global Partnership Program, we've created a series of strategic resources to support our listed companies' growth initiatives, and act as a conduit that enables them to reach new and important audiences. The NYSE Global Partnership Program is designed to provide our listed companies with a turnkey extension to their worldwide promotional and media relations activities.|url=https://www.nyse.com/about/listed/1224887730297.html|access-date=2017-09-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110703044410/http://www.nyse.com/about/listed/1224887730297.html|archive-date=2011-07-03|url-status=dead}}</ref> NYSE Euronext's 8,000 listed issues provide members with an extensive network of global investors and business leaders with which to interact. The company offers opportunities for co-branded advertising, linking listed companies to one another, as well as to the powerful brand that is NYSE Euronext.<ref>{{cite web|title=Strategic placement of corporate messaging will help extend the reach of your company's brand and its NYSE-listed status in an engaging way. Several opportunities are available for NYSE listed companies including subway, Times Square and Elevator advertising programs.|url=https://www.nyse.com/exccelerate/visibility/brand-activation.html|access-date=2017-09-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130526213153/http://www.nyse.com/exccelerate/visibility/brand-activation.html|archive-date=2013-05-26|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n===Events===\n\nThe [https://web.archive.org/web/20120219085114/http://www.nyx.com/eventrental/faq Events] department of NYSE Euronext is responsible for coordinating bell ceremonies, receptions, conferences, and street events. Beginning in 2010, the NYSE Euronext opened its doors to non-listed companies to utilize NYSE facilities for after-hours events.\n\n====Opening and closing ceremonies====\n\nThe opening and closing bell ceremonies hosted by the NYSE date back to 1903, taking place Monday through Friday at 9:30&nbsp;a.m. and 4:00&nbsp;p.m. respectively in New York City.\n\nThe opportunity to ring the bell at the New York Stock Exchange has long been considered an honor. Representatives from listed companies, especially newly listed companies and [[initial public offering|IPOs]], celebrities, politicians, and other dignitaries have become fixtures at the bell podium. Bell ceremonies are seen by millions, and are the most widely watched TV events each day.\n\nThe bell tradition has been extended to the branches in Paris, Brussels, and Lisbon. In Amsterdam, the opening bell was replaced by a [[gong]], which is sounded the signal the beginning and end of the trading day. In the European offices, the opening and closing ceremonies take place at 9:00&nbsp;a.m. and 5:30&nbsp;p.m., respectively.<ref>{{cite web|title=Bell ceremony overview|url=http://www.euronext.com/editorial/wide/editorial-21967-EN.html|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111207233945/http://www.euronext.com/editorial/wide/editorial-21967-EN.html|archivedate=2011-12-07}}</ref>\n\n====Experience Square====\nThe Broad Street area in front of the Exchange is known as Experience Square,{{citation needed|date=June 2015}} where listed companies are able to market themselves and their products directly to the thousands of visitors to New York's Financial District each day. The fa\u00e7ade of the exchange is often used as a billboard to showcase branding and new listings.{{citation needed|date=June 2015}}\n\n====''NYSE Magazine''====\n\n''NYSE Magazine'' is NYSE Euronext's quarterly publication. It provides insights into the world\u2019s best companies, giving readers a close-up look at the distinguished leaders who constitute the Exchange community. Written for a sophisticated audience of CEOs and other senior global executives, each issue centers on what makes companies succeed. Designed to foster a sense of community among the NYSE\u2019s key constituents, NYSE magazine has grown to become a strategic tool for business leaders that delivers opinions, strategies and insights from their peers. Extended articles, Q&As, videos, photo, and slideshows are now available at www.nysemagazine.com and on [[iPad]] via the NYSE magazine app. NYSE magazine print and digital editions reach thousands of opinion leaders around the globe, including top management of publicly traded and private companies, government officials, the financial community and the media.  NYSE ceased production of the print edition in 2013 and currently publishes content exclusively online.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|http://www.nyx.com/}}\n* [http://www.cbc.ca/news/story/2006/03/08/nyse-060308.html \"NYSE stock soars 25 per cent after it goes public for first time in 214 years\"], [[CBC News]], 2006-03-08\n\n{{NYSE Euronext}}\n{{Stock exchanges top 18}}\n{{World Federation of Exchanges}}\n{{Portal|Companies}}\n{{authority control}}\n[[Category:Companies formerly listed on the New York Stock Exchange]]\n[[Category:NYSE Euronext| ]]\n[[Category:2007 establishments in New York City]]\n[[Category:Companies based in Manhattan]]\n[[Category:American companies established in 2007]]\n[[Category:Companies disestablished in 2013]]\n[[Category:Defunct companies of the United States]]\n[[Category:Financial services companies based in New York City]]\n[[Category:Multinational companies based in New York City]]\n[[Category:Options exchanges in the United States]]\n[[Category:2013 mergers and acquisitions]]\n[[Category:Companies formed by merger]]\n", "text_old": "{{more citations needed|date=January 2013}}\n{{Infobox company\n|name = NYSE Euronext, Inc.\n|logo = [[File:NYSE Euronext 2012 logo.svg|200px|The NYSE Euronext logo as of 2012.]]\n|type = Subsidiary\n|predecessors = NYSE Group, Inc.<br />Euronext N.V.\n|industry = [[Financial services]]\n|foundation = {{Start date|2007|04|4}}\n|defunct = 2013\n|location_city = [[Wall Street|11 Wall Street]], [[New York City|New York]], [[New York (state)]]\n|location_country = [[United States]]  \n|area_served = United States, European Union\n|fate = Acquired by [[Intercontinental Exchange]], [[Euronext]] later spun off\n|key_people = [[Duncan L. Niederauer]]<br>(CEO) \n|services = [[Derivative (finance)|Derivatives]], [[equity trading]] platforms, [[Futures contract|futures]] and [[Option (finance)|options]] [[Financial market|markets]], [[market data]], [[Stock exchange|securities exchanges]]\n|revenue = US$ 3.75 billion (2013)<ref name=\"AR2010\">{{cite web |url=https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1368007/000136800713000005/nyx-20121231x10k.htm/item=UGFyZW50SUQ9MzU2NjUzM3xDaGlsZElEPTQxMjc4MHxUeXBlPTI=&t=1|title=Annual Results 2010|publisher=NYSE Euronext|accessdate=27 February 2011}}</ref>\n|operating_income = US$ {{0|0}}850&nbsp;million (2011)<ref name=\"AR2010\"/>\n|net_income = US$ {{0|0}}619&nbsp;million (2011)<ref name=\"AR2010\"/>\n|assets = US$ 13.07&nbsp;billion (2011)<ref name=\"AR2010\"/>\n|equity = US$ 6.581&nbsp;billion (2011)<ref name=\"AR2010\"/>\n|num_employees = 3,061 (2012)<ref name=\"AR2010\"/>\n|divisions = [[New York Stock Exchange]],<br />[[Euronext]] ([[Euronext Amsterdam|Amsterdam]], [[Euronext Paris|Paris]], [[Euronext Brussels|Brussels]], [[Euronext Lisbon|Lisbon]]),<br />[[NYSE Arca]], [[Euronext.liffe|NYSE Liffe]], [[NYSE Technologies]]\n|parent = [[Intercontinental Exchange]]\n|homepage = {{URL|http://www.nyx.com|NYX.com}}\n}}\n\n'''NYSE Euronext, Inc.''' was a Euro-American [[Multinational corporation|multinational]] [[financial services]] corporation that operated multiple [[Stock exchange|securities exchanges]], including the [[New York Stock Exchange]], [[Euronext]] and [[NYSE Arca]] (formerly known as ArcaEx). NYSE merged with Archipelago Holdings on March 7, 2006, forming NYSE Group, Inc.<ref>{{cite web|title=\"Archipelago\" refers to, prior to and following the completion of its merger with the New York Stock Exchange, Inc., which occurred on March 7, 2006, Archipelago Holdings, Inc., a Delaware corporation, and, where the context requires, its predecessor, Archipelago Holdings, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company;|url=https://www.nyse.com/pdfs/10Q_08.PDF|publisher=NYSE|access-date=2017-09-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130526202707/http://www.nyse.com/pdfs/10Q_08.PDF|archive-date=2013-05-26|url-status=dead}}</ref> On April 4, 2007, NYSE Group, Inc. merged with Euronext N.V. to form the first global equities exchange, with its headquarters in [[Lower Manhattan]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.businessweek.com/ap/financialnews/D9LDDVSO1.htm |title=NYSE, Deutsche Boerse are already global companies|author=Pallavi Gogoi|date=February 15, 2011<!--, 3:20PM ET -->|publisher=[[Bloomberg Businessweek]]|accessdate=February 5, 2012}}</ref> The corporation was then acquired by [[Intercontinental Exchange]], which subsequently spun off Euronext.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://dealbook.nytimes.com/2014/05/27/intercontinentalexchange-announces-plans-to-float-euronext/|title=IntercontinentalExchange Set to Spin Off Euronext|author=Chad Bray|date=May 27, 2014|work=[[New York Times]]|accessdate=August 25, 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Overview==\nNYSE Euronext offers a broad and growing array of financial products and services in cash equities, [[futures contract|futures]], [[option (finance)|option]]s, [[exchange-traded product]]s (ETPs), [[bond (finance)|bond]]s, market data, and commercial technology. Spanning multiple asset classes and six countries, the company's exchanges include the New York Stock Exchange, Liffe, Euronext and NYSE Arca.  With more than 8,000<ref>{{cite web|title=With approximately 8,000 listed issues (excluding European Structured Products), NYSE Euronext's equities markets \u2013 the New York Stock Exchange, NYSE Euronext, NYSE Amex, NYSE Alternext and NYSE Arca \u2013 represent one-third of the world's equities trading, the most liquidity of any global exchange group|url=https://www.nyse.com/press/1310637000012.html|access-date=2017-09-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140217042551/http://www.nyse.com/press/1310637000012.html|archive-date=2014-02-17|url-status=dead}}</ref> listed issues (which includes 90% of the [[Dow Jones Industrial Average]] and 80% of the [[S&P 500]],<ref>{{cite web|title=19.90% of the Dow Jones Industrial Average; 80% of the S&P 500|url=https://www.nyse.com/exccelerate/community/company-you-keep.html|access-date=2017-09-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130526200048/http://www.nyse.com/exccelerate/community/company-you-keep.html|archive-date=2013-05-26|url-status=dead}}</ref> trading on NYSE Euronext's equity markets represents more than one-third of the world's cash equities volume. The company also manages the leading European derivatives exchange by value of trading.\n\nNYSE Euronext is part of the S&P 500 index and the only exchange operator in the [[S&P 100|S&P 100 index]].<ref>{{cite web|title=NYSE Euronext is in the S&P 500 index, and is the only exchange operator in the S&P 100 index and Fortune 500.|url=http://www.nyseblue.com/news/pr-NYSE-Euronext-and-APX-Complete-Transaction-and-form-NYSE-Blue.htm|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120226170212/http://www.nyseblue.com/news/pr-NYSE-Euronext-and-APX-Complete-Transaction-and-form-NYSE-Blue.htm|archivedate=2012-02-26}}</ref>\n\nNYSE Euronext is a [[Delaware]] corporation, though the principal executive office of NYSE Euronext is located at 11 Wall Street, New York, New York 10005. The European headquarters are at 39 Rue Cambon, 75001 in [[Paris]], [[France]].\n\n==Locations==\nBelow is a list of major NYSE Euronext locations:\n* [[Amsterdam]], [[Netherlands]]\n* [[Belfast]], [[Northern Ireland]]\n* [[Brussels]], [[Belgium]]\n* [[Chicago]], [[Illinois]], [[United States of America]]\n* [[Lisbon]], [[Portugal]]\n* [[London]], [[United Kingdom]]\n* [[New York City]], [[New York State|New York]], [[United States of America]]\n* [[Palo Alto]], [[California]], [[United States of America]]\n* [[Paris]], [[France]]\n* [[San Francisco]], [[California]], [[United States of America]]\n\n==Mergers and acquisitions==\n\n===NYSE and Archipelago Holdings===\n[https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2005/12/06/AR2005120601744.html The merger between NYSE and Archipelago Holdings] was initially approved in 2005 by a 95% majority of voting NYSE members.<ref>{{cite news|title=About 90 percent of the Big Board's 1,366 members voted, and 95 percent of those voted in favor of the merger.|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2005/12/06/AR2005120601744.html | work=The Washington Post | first1=Dean|last1=Starkman|first2=Ben|last2=White|date=December 7, 2005}}</ref> The acquisition of Archipelago, which held possession of highly regarded market technology at the time, was intended to bring automated trading to NYSE markets (which had previously utilized an \"[[open outcry]]\" system) and increase efficiency.\n\nFor the first time in its 213-year history, the New York Stock Exchange became a for-profit company, and began trading publicly on its own stock exchange under the NYX ticker.<ref>{{cite news|title=The New York Stock Exchange voted to acquire a Chicago-based electronic stock-exchange company, Archipelago Holdings Inc., in a historic step that will transform the 213-year-old Big Board from a tradition-bound concern owned by and for its members to a profit-seeking, publicly traded company expected to compete in the evolving world of electronic markets.|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2005/12/06/AR2005120601744.html | work=The Washington Post | first1=Dean|last1=Starkman|first2=Ben|last2=White|date=December 7, 2005}}</ref> Owners of the 1,366 NYSE seats received 80,177 shares of NYSE Group stock plus $300,000 in cash and $70,571 in dividends for each seat.<ref>{{cite web|title=Under the final agreement, owners of the 1,366 seats on the NYSE received 80,177 shares of NYSE Group stock plus $300,000 in cash and another $70,571 in dividends.|url=http://www.nbcnews.com/id/11725095}}</ref> The completion of this deal created two new branches of the NYSE Group: NYSE Arca and NYSE Arca Europe, which launched after the acquisition of Euronext.\n\n===NYSE Group and Euronext merger April 4, 2007===\n[[File:Logo of NYSE Euronext 2007-2012.svg|thumb|Logo used between 2007 and 2012]]\nIn April 2006, NYSE Group and Euronext signed a merger agreement, subject to shareholder vote and regulatory approval.<ref>{{cite web|title=On April 3, 2007, NYSE Group and Euronext completed their historical business combination to create NYSE Euronext, the world's leading and most liquid exchange group.|url=https://www.nyse.com/about/newsevents/1175510198386}}{{Dead link|date=September 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> Euronext shareholders gave approval to the transaction on December 19, 2006, and shareholders from the NYSE Group followed suit one day later.<ref>{{cite web |title=Approximately 99.7 percent of NYSE Group, Inc. (NYSE: NYX) shareholders who voted have approved the Exchange's proposed combination with Euronext N.V., whose shareholders yesterday approved this historic transaction that creates the first truly global exchange group. |url=https://www.nyse.com/press/1166613560168.html |date=December 20, 2006 <!-- |accessdate=February 2013 --> |series=Press Release |publisher=New York Stock Exchange (NYSE) |access-date=2017-09-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130526210020/http://www.nyse.com/press/1166613560168.html |archive-date=2013-05-26 |url-status=dead }}</ref> In April 2007 the Euronext shareholders tendering shares can receive NYSE shares and cash amounting to $11,141 million from NYSE Euronext for their assets.<ref>{{cite web |title=NYSEGgroup and EURONEXT N.V. agree to a merger of Equals. Combination Will Create The First Global Exchange; Joint Press/Analyst Conference Scheduled in Paris, Friday, June 2, 2006. |url=http://www1.nyse.com/press/1149157439121.html |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130625020945/http://www.nyse.com/press/1149157439121.html |archivedate=June 25, 2013 }}</ref> About 94% of the 112,557,259 shares are tendered in the first round.<ref>Euronext N.V. Annual report for the year 2007</ref>\n\nThe NYSE Group and Euronext merger on April 4, 2007, signaled the creation of the world's largest and most [[Liquidity|liquid]] exchange group\u2014NYSE Euronext.<ref name=NYSE20070405>{{cite web |title=NYSE Euronext (NYSE/New York and Euronext/Paris: NYX) and offers the most diverse array of financial products and services. |url=https://www.nyse.com/about/newsevents/1149243292355.html |date=April 5, 2007<!-- |accessdate=February 2013 --> |series=Press Release |publisher=New York Stock Exchange (NYSE) |access-date=2017-09-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110319022431/http://www.nyse.com/about/newsevents/1149243292355.html |archive-date=2011-03-19 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n===NYSE Euronext and NYFIX===\nNYSE Euronext, through its wholly owned subsidiary NYSE Technologies, Inc. acquired  NYFIX, Inc. (Nasdaq: NYFX) for $144 million in November 2009. NYSE Euronext incorporated NYFIX's trading software into the company's package of offerings to customers.<ref name=NYSE20090827>{{cite web |location=New York |date=August 27, 2009 |url=https://www.nyse.com/press/1251367635488.html |title=NYSE Euronext's acquisition of NYFIX <!-- |accessdate=February 2013 --> |access-date=2017-09-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130526202023/http://www.nyse.com/press/1251367635488.html |archive-date=2013-05-26 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n===Attempted merger between NYSE Euronext and Deutsche B\u00f6rse===\nIn 2011, ''[[Bloomberg L.P.|Bloomberg]]'' reported that the German exchange operator [[Deutsche B\u00f6rse]] was in advanced talks to buy NYSE Euronext for $9.53 billion in a deal that would create the world's largest trading powerhouse.<ref>{{cite web|title=Deutsche Boerse AG's $9.53 billion all-stock purchase of New York Stock Exchange parent NYSE Euronext creates the world's largest owner of equities and derivatives markets, and may spur additional mergers.|url=http://www.businessweek.com/news/2011-02-15/deutsche-boerse-9-53-billion-nyse-buy-may-spur-deals}}</ref> The shares of both companies were temporarily frozen on the news due to the risk of large price movements and clarifications of the deal. A successful deal would see the new company becoming the world's largest stock exchange operator with a market capitalization of listed companies equal to $15 trillion.<ref>{{cite web|title=While the merged entity will list corporations with about $15 trillion in value, more than any other exchange, what may prove more lucrative is ownership of growing venues for trading futures and options, said Rich Repetto, a New York-based analyst at Sandler O'Neill & Partners LP.|url=http://www.businessweek.com/news/2011-02-15/deutsche-boerse-9-53-billion-nyse-buy-may-spur-deals}}</ref>\n\nThe proposed group would have dual headquarters, in Deutsche Boerse's newly built green tower near [[Frankfurt]], [[Germany]], and in New York City at 11 Wall Street. It would be led by a board with seventeen members\u2014fifteen directors plus the Chairman and the CEO. Of the fifteen directors, nine to be designated by Deutsche Boerse and six by NYSE Euronext. Current NYSE Euronext CEO Duncan Niederauer would assume the same role with the newly founded company and would lead an Executive Committee with an equal number of current Deutsche Boerse and NYSE Euronext executives.<ref>{{cite web|title=The group will have dual headquarters, in Deutsche Boerse's newly built green tower near Frankfurt and in New York, at 11 Wall Street, home to the iconic New York Stock Exchange trading floor, and would take advantage of its existing global operations. The Company would be led by a one-tier board with 17 members \u2013 15 directors plus the Chairman and the CEO. Of the fifteen directors, nine would be designated by Deutsche Boerse and six by NYSE Euronext. Reto Francioni would be Chairman, and would also be responsible for group strategy and global relationship management. Duncan Niederauer would be Chief Executive Officer and would lead an Executive Committee with an equal number of current Deutsche Boerse and NYSE Euronext executives.|url=http://ir.nyse.com/phoenix.zhtml?c=129145&p=irol-newsArticle&ID=1529114}}</ref>\n\nOn July 7, 2011, NYSE Euronext shareholders voted in favor of the merger, and on July 13, 2011, Deutsche Boerse shareholders approved the deal as well. These decisions move the two sides closer to completing the transaction, which must still pass through forty separate regulatory approval processes to be finalized.<ref>{{cite news|title=Deutsche Boerse AG (DB1.XE) on Thursday secured shareholder backing for its planned merger with NYSE Euronext (NYX), focusing attention on efforts to win regulatory clearance for what would be the world's largest exchange operator. Investors in both companies placed faith in the ability of exchange executives to shepherd the combination through a gauntlet of more than 40 separate regulatory approval processes \u2013 including a lengthy review by the European Union \u2013 without ceding too many concessions that might dilute is planned benefits. |url=https://online.wsj.com/article/BT-CO-20110714-710899.html }}{{dead link|date=June 2016|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref>\n\nThe merger was subject to review in both the United States and with the European Union (EU) for concerns it could create a \u201c[[de facto monopoly|''de facto'' monopoly]]\u201d.\n \nIn October 2011, CEO Niederauer said the company had received the EU's so-called statement of objections, which was more than 100 pages long, and would be responding within two weeks, possibly by asking for the opportunity for an oral hearing with the regulators. The EU examination of the proposal formally began June 29 has said its expanded probe has a Dec. 13 deadline. In March, [[Joaquin Almunia]], the EU's antitrust commissioner, expressed concern that the deal would maybe monopolize the derivatives market due to Deutsche Boerse's \u201cvertical silo\u201d which routes all trade clearing through its own services. Almunia said then he preferred a \u201cmore open business model\u201d for markets.<ref>Rummer, Andrew, and Peter Chapman, editors, [http://news.businessweek.com/article.asp?documentKey=1376-LSYAH56K50Y601-09845DBNU4QT522C0IPVDS93NA \"NYSE Euronext May Seek EU Hearing to Defend Deutsche Boerse Deal\"]{{dead link|date=December 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}, ''Bloomberg'', October 13, 2011 11:06 am EDT. Retrieved 2011-10-13.</ref>\n\nOn December 22, 2011, Deutsche Boerse won U.S. antitrust approval to buy NYSE Euronext, on condition that a Deutsche Boerse subsidiary, the International Securities Exchange, divest its 31.5 percent interest in [[Direct Edge]].<ref>[https://www.reuters.com/article/2011/12/22/us-nyse-deutscheboerse-idUSTRE7BL1CE20111222 Deutsche Boerse (DB1Gn.DE) won U.S. antitrust approval to buy NYSE Euronext (NYX.N) in a $9 billion deal to create the world's No. 1 exchange operator, but the transaction still faces serious regulatory headwinds in Europe.] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150914053146/https://www.reuters.com/article/2011/12/22/us-nyse-deutscheboerse-idUSTRE7BL1CE20111222 |date=September 14, 2015 }}, ''Reuters'', Dec 22, 2011. Retrieved 09-01-2012.</ref> NYSE Euronext and Deutsche Boerse AG delayed the deadline for completing their merger until March 31, 2012 so the exchange operators could try to persuade European regulators to approve the deal.<ref>[https://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-27/nyse-euronext-deutsche-boerse-merger-date-extended-to-march-31.html NYSE, Deutsche Boerse Merger Date Extended] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131103085042/http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-27/nyse-euronext-deutsche-boerse-merger-date-extended-to-march-31.html |date=November 3, 2013 }}, ''Bloomberg'', Dec 28, 2011. Retrieved 09-01-2012.</ref>\n\nOn February 1, 2012, the European Union blocked the planned merger between NYSE Euronext and Deutsche Boerse. The European Commission\u2014the EU's executive body\u2014ruled against the merger because, they said, the combined exchange would control more than 90% of the trade in European derivatives. The European Commission report stated, \"The merger between Deutsche Boerse and NYSE Euronext would have led to a near-monopoly in European financial derivatives worldwide... These markets are at the heart of the financial system and it is crucial for the whole European economy that they remain competitive\".<ref>[https://www.npr.org/2012/02/01/146215168/, EU blocks Deutsche Boerse NYSE Euronext merger]{{dead link|date=December 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}, ''The Associated Press'', Feb 1, 2012. Retrieved 2012-02-01.</ref>\n\nOn February 2, 2012, the NYSE Euronext and Deutsche B\u00f6rse agreed with strong opposition by the EU for the planned merger, to scrap the merger.<ref>[https://www.nyse.com/press/1328178461772.html NYSE Euronext Press Release] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150712071646/http://www.nyse.com/press/1328178461772.html |date=July 12, 2015 }}</ref>\n\n===Intercontinental Exchange acquisition of NYSE Euronext===\nOn December 20, 2012, the boards of directors of both [[Intercontinental Exchange]] (ICE) and the NYSE Euronext approved an $8 billion acquisition of NYSE Euronext. Under the terms shareholders of NYSE would receive either $33.12 in cash for each share or .2581 IntercontinentalExchange Inc. shares, or a combination of $11.27 in cash per share plus .1703 shares of stock.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.cbsnews.com/8301-505123_162-57560197/intercontinentalexchange-to-buy-nyse-for-$8.2b/ |via=[[CBS News]] |publisher=[[Associated Press]] |title=IntercontinentalExchange to buy NYSE for $8.2B |date=December 20, 2012 |accessdate=August 25, 2014}}</ref> The acquisition is subject to regulator approval, though since the operations of ICE and NYSE have little in common\u2014ICE is largely devoted to trading commodities, as opposed to NYSE's business of trading stocks and securities\u2014the deal is not expected to be blocked.<ref name=\"nytimes\">{{cite news | url=https://dealbook.nytimes.com/2012/12/20/upstart-market-operator-clinches-8-2-billion-deal-for-n-y-s-e/?hp | title=Upstart Market Operator Clinches $8.2 Billion Deal for N.Y.S.E. | work=The New York Times | date=December 20, 2012 | accessdate=December 20, 2012}}</ref> ICE said that after the deal closed it would sell the Euronext portion of the company, including stock exchanges in Amsterdam, Brussels, Lisbon and Paris.<ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-20802445 | title=NYSE agrees to be sold to rival ICE for $8bn | publisher=BBC News Online | date=December 20, 2012 | accessdate=December 20, 2012}}</ref>  The deal went through and Euronext is a sister division to NYSE and part of ICE. ICE CEO [[Jeffrey C. Sprecher]] would continue in that position at the combined company, while NYSE CEO Duncan Niederauer would serve as president.<ref name=\"nytimes\"/>  The future of the New York Stock Exchange's historic trading floor under ICE has not been announced.  ICE closed the high profile and historic trading floors of its other earlier acquisitions\u2014the [[International Petroleum Exchange]] and the [[New York Board of Trade]] in New York.<ref name=\"nytimes1\">{{cite news| url=https://www.nytimes.com/2013/01/20/business/jeffrey-sprechers-improbable-path-to-buying-the-nyse.html?partner=rss&emc=rss&pagewanted=print | work=The New York Times | first=Nathaniel | last=Popper | title=Jeffrey Sprecher's Improbable Path to Buying the N.Y.S.E | date=January 19, 2013}}</ref>\n\n==Company structure==\n===Derivatives===\nThe Derivatives segment consists of NYSE Euronext's derivatives trading and clearing businesses. This includes [[NYSE Liffe]], NYSE Liffe Clearing, NYSE Liffe US, [[NYSE Amex]] Options, NYSE Arca Option, and related derivatives market data.<ref name=\"annual report\">{{cite web|title=NYSE Euronext annual report|url=http://phx.corporate-ir.net/External.File?item=UGFyZW50SUQ9ODU5NzN8Q2hpbGRJRD0tMXxUeXBlPTM=&t=1}}</ref>\n\n====NYSE Liffe====\nNYSE Liffe comprises the derivatives market operated by LIFFE Administration and Management, Euronext Amsterdam, Euronext Brussels, Euronext Lisbon, and Euronext Paris. It offers customers the advantages of one of the most technologically advanced derivatives trading platforms as well as one of the widest choices of products of any derivatives market.<ref name=\"annual report\"/>\n\nThrough a single [[electronic trading platform]], NYSE Liffe offers customers access to a wide range of [[Interest rate|interest-rate]], [[Equity (finance)|equity]], [[Stock market index|index]], [[commodity]] and currency derivative products. This platform has been designed to handle significant order flows and transaction volumes. Orders can be matched either on a price/time or pro rata basis, configurable by contract, with transacted prices and volumes and the aggregate size of all bids and offers at each price level updated on a real-time basis. Users can continually notified of all active orders in the central order book, making market depth easy to monitor.<ref name=\"annual report\"/>\n\nNYSE Liffe also offers its customers the Bclear and Cscreen services, which bridge the listed and [[Over-the-counter (finance)|over-the-counter]] (OTC) markets. This provides a simple and cost-effective way to register and process wholesale derivatives trades through NYSE Liffe to clearing at NYSE Liffe Clearing. Following the launch of NYSE Liffe Clearing, NYSE Liffe assumed full responsibility for clearing activities on its own London market.<ref name=\"annual report\"/>\n\nNYSE Liffe US, NYSE Euronext's U.S. futures exchange, makes available for trading full- and mini-sized gold and silver futures, options on full-sized gold and silver futures and futures on [[Morgan Stanley Capital International]] (MSCI) Indices. A significant minority equity stake in NYSE Liffe US is held by six external investors: [[Citadel|Citadel Securities]], DRW Investments, [[Global Electronic Trading Company|Getco]], [[Goldman Sachs]], [[Morgan Stanley]] and [[UBS]]. Under this ownership structure, NYSE Euronext remains the largest shareholder in the entity and consolidates its financial reporting. NYSE Euronext manages the day-to-day operations of NYSE Liffe US, which operates under the supervision of a separate board of directors.<ref name=\"annual report\"/>\n\n====NYSE Amex Options====\nThe NYSE Amex Options business uses a hybrid model combining both auction-based and electronic trading capabilities that is designed to provide a stable, liquid and less volatile market. This feature provides the opportunity for price and/or size improvement.<ref name=\"annual report\"/>\n\nIn 2010, NYSE Euronext announced the sale of a significant equity interest in NYSE Amex Options to seven external investors: [[Bank of America Merrill Lynch]], [[Barclays Capital]], Citadel Securities, [[Citi]], Goldman Sachs, [[TD Ameritrade]], and UBS. Under the framework, NYSE Euronext remains the largest shareholder in the entity and manages the day-to-day operations of NYSE Amex Options, which operates under the supervision of a separate board of directors and chief executive officer. NYSE Euronext consolidates this entity for financial reporting purposes.<ref name=\"annual report\"/>\n\n====NYSE Arca Options====\nNYSE Arca Options, the other of NYSE Euronext's two U.S. options exchanges, offers immediate, cost-effective electronic order execution in nearly two thousand options issues. The NYSE Arca Options business uses a technology platform and market structure designed to enhance the speed and quality of trade execution for its customers, as well as to attract additional sources of liquidity. Its structure allows market makers to access its markets remotely and integrates floor-based participants as well.<ref name=\"annual report\"/>\n\n===Cash Trading and Listings===\nThe Cash Trading and Listings segment includes the New York Stock Exchange, Euronext, NYSE Amex, NYSE Arca, NYSE Alternext, NYSE Arca Europe, SmartPool, [[BlueNext]], and NYSE Blue, as well as related cash trading market data.<ref name=\"annual report\"/>\n\n====New York Stock Exchange====\nThe [[New York Stock Exchange]] is registered as a national securities exchange under the [[Exchange Act]]. In addition to common stock, preferred stock and [[warrant (finance)|warrants]], the NYSE lists debt and corporate structured products, such as capital securities, mandatory convertibles, and repackaged securities.<ref name=\"annual report\"/>\n\n====Euronext====\n[[Euronext]] is the first integrated cross-border exchange, combining the stock exchanges of Amsterdam, Paris, Brussels and Lisbon into a single market. Issuers who meet [[European Union]] regulatory standards are qualified for listing on the regulated markets operated by Euronext. The company's exchanges list a wide variety of securities, including domestic and international equity securities, convertible bonds, warrants, trackers and debt securities, including corporate and government bonds.<ref name=\"annual report\"/>\n\nAll of Euronext's markets are operated by its subsidiaries, each of which holds a national license as an exchange operator.<ref name=\"annual report\"/>\n\n====NYSE Amex====\nNYSE Euronext completed its acquisition of the [[American Stock Exchange|Amex]] (American Stock Exchange) on October 1, 2008. The transaction extended NYSE Euronext's leadership in U.S. option, cash equities, and [[exchange-traded fund]]s (ETFs), making it the third largest U.S. equity options marketplace based on number of contracts traded. Since the merger, Amex has been integrated into the company, with former Amex listings now trading directly on the NYSE, and has begun trading certain [[Nasdaq]]-listed securities.<ref name=\"annual report\"/>\n\nNYSE Arca is the first electronic market to offer listed ETP issuers a Lead Market Maker program, which encourages liquidity provision that contributes to the best prices and depth in the ETP marketplace. It is registered as a national securities exchange under the Exchange Act.<ref name=\"annual report\"/>\n\n====NYSE Alternext====\n\n[[NYSE Alternext]] was created by NYSE Euronext to meet the needs of small and mid-sized companies seeking simplified access to the stock market. Its streamlined listing requirements and trading rules are suited to the size and business needs of such firms. The rules also ensure investor transparency. NYSE Alternext's special listing procedures, unique market model, and listings of sponsor companies for members are its most notable features.<ref name=\"annual report\"/>\n\nNYSE Alternext is an exchange-regulated market with a lighter regulatory regime. It is not a regulated market as defined by the [[Markets in Financial Instruments Directive]] (MiFID), but rather is regulated by NYSE Euronext through a body of rules applicable to intermediaries and listed companies.<ref name=\"annual report\"/>\n\n====NYSE Arca Europe====\nNYSE Arca Europe is a pan-European [[multilateral trading facility]] (MTF) that extends the trading scope of Euronext's regulated markets by adding [[Blue chip (stock market)|blue-chip]] stocks from 14 European countries: [[Austria]], [[Czech Republic]], [[Denmark]], [[Finland]], [[France]], [[Germany]], [[Hungary]], [[Ireland]], [[Italy]], [[Norway]], [[Spain]], [[Sweden]], [[Switzerland]], and the United Kingdom. Arca Europe integrates this trading facility with the other business components of the company, giving customers the flexibility in trading of an MTF while maintaining the global market reach of NYSE Euronext.<ref name=\"annual report\"/>\n\n====SmartPool====\n[https://web.archive.org/web/20120426060115/http://www.tradeonsmartpool.com/ SmartPool Trading Limited] is a UK-registered company supplying an MTF approved by the [[Financial Services Authority]] (FSA). It provides an exchange-led dark pool for the execution of block orders covering 15 different European markets, with a full central counter party back-end through [[LCH.Clearnet]] and EuroCCP. SmartPool was created by NYSE Euronext in partnership with [[BNP Paribas]], [[HSBC]], and [[J.P. Morgan Chase]].<ref name=\"annual report\"/>\n\n====BlueNext and NYSE Blue====\nNYSE Euronext holds a 60% interest in [[BlueNext]] with the remaining 40% held by CDC Climat. BlueNext operates a spot market in carbon dioxide emission allowances and credits that is the European leader in the field. It seeks to establish a leading position in trading in environment-related instruments, and has also launched a futures market with physical delivery of allowances and credits.<ref name=\"annual report\"/>\n\nIn September 2010, NYSE Euronext announced plans to create NYSE Blue, a new global company that will focus on environmental and sustainable energy markets. NYSE Euronext contributed its ownership in BlueNext in return for a majority interest in NYSE Blue, and [[APX|APX, Inc.]] (a leading provider of regulatory infrastructure and services for environmental and sustainable energy markets) will contribute its business in return for a minority interest in the venture. The transaction closed on February 18, 2011.<ref name=\"annual report\"/>\n\n===Information Services and Technology Solutions===\n\nThe Information Services and Technology Solutions segment refers to NYSE Euronext's commercial technology transactions, data, and infrastructure businesses. NYSE Euronext operates NYSE Technologies, Free Market, and also owns NYFIX, Inc.<ref name=\"annual report\"/>\n\n====NYSE Technologies====\n\n[[NYSE Technologies]] is the commercial technology division of NYSE Euronext.<ref name=\"annual report\"/>\n\nNYSE Technologies operates five business:\n* '''Global Market Data''' offers a broad array of global market information products covering multiple asset classes;\n* '''Trading Solutions''' creates and implements high performance, end-to-end messaging software, real-time market data distribution and integration products;\n* '''Exchange Solutions''' provides multi-asset exchange platform services, managed services and expert consultancy;\n* '''Global Connectivity''' offers one of the world's largest, most reliable financial transaction networks connecting firms and exchanges worldwide;\n* '''Transactions''' primarily comprises the former NYFIX FIX business and incorporates the NYFIX Marketplace and the FIX Software business.\n\n====March\u00e9 Libre====\n\nThe Free Markets of Brussels and Paris, organized by NYSE Euronext, are not regulated markets in the sense of the EU Directive. The criteria for admission to these markets are much simpler, and listing costs are low. They provide a channel for disseminating buy and sell orders, with trades executed by NYSE Euronext member firms. The securities traded on these markets have not gone through any admission procedures and issuers are not subject to any disclosure requirements. The Free Markets serve companies that are too young or too small to be listed on one of the regulated compartments of NYSE Euronext.<ref name=\"annual report\"/>\n\n====NYSE Regulation and FINRA====\nOn May 4, 2010, NYSE Euronext and the [[Financial Industry Regulatory Authority]] (FINRA) announced that FINRA would assume responsibility for performing the [[market surveillance]] and enforcement functions originally conducted by NYSE Regulation. The agreement was subject to review by the [[Securities and Exchange Commission]] (SEC) and was completed in June 2010.<ref name=\"annual report\"/>\n\nUnder the announced agreement, FINRA assumed regulatory functions for NYSE Euronext's U.S. equities and options markets \u2013 the New York Stock Exchange, NYSE Arca, and NYSE Amex. NYSE Euronext, through its subsidiary NYSE Regulation, remains ultimately responsible for overseeing FINRA's performance of regulatory services for the NYSE markets.<ref name=\"annual report\"/>\n\n===Libor administration===\nIn early 2014, NYSE Euronext took over the administration of the [[London interbank offered rate]] from the [[British Bankers Association]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nyse.com/press/1373365567815.html|title=NYSE EURONEXT SUBSIDIARY TO BECOME NEW ADMINISTRATOR OF LIBOR|publisher=NYSE Euronext|date=2013-07-09|accessdate=2013-07-21|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130718141355/http://www.nyse.com/press/1373365567815.html|archivedate=2013-07-18}}</ref> The new administrator is NYSE Euronext Rates Administration Limited,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bba.org.uk/media/article/bba-to-hand-over-administration-of-libor-to-nyse-euronext-rate-administrati|title=BBA to hand over administration of LIBOR to NYSE Euronext Rate Administration Limited|publisher=The British Bankers\u2019 Association|date=2013-07-09|accessdate=2013-07-20|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130713075451/http://www.bba.org.uk/media/article/bba-to-hand-over-administration-of-libor-to-nyse-euronext-rate-administrati|archivedate=2013-07-13}}</ref> a London-based, UK registered company, regulated by the UK\u2019s [[Financial Conduct Authority]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cityam.com/article/libor-now-has-new-administrator-our-reforms-have-gone-much-further|title=Libor now has a new administrator \u2013 but our reforms have gone much further|author=Anthony Browne, chief executive of the British Bankers\u2019 Association|publisher=City A.M.|date=2013-07-11|accessdate=2013-07-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131104030713/http://www.cityam.com/article/libor-now-has-new-administrator-our-reforms-have-gone-much-further|archive-date=2013-11-04|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n==Global marketing and branding==\n\nNYSE Euronext maintains an active marketing campaign, both for its own brand, as well as for its listed companies. The Global Marketing and Branding department is responsible for the full spectrum of NYSE Euronext's brand marketing, including advertising, marketing communications, event management, and market research.<ref>{{cite web|title=As the Global Head of Marketing & Branding for NYSE Euronext, Marisa Ricciardi plays a key role in the strategic development and implementation of the company's branding and communications. Her group is responsible for the full spectrum of NYSE Euronext's brand marketing, including advertising, marketing communications, event management and market research targeting a range of constituents across the globe|url=http://exchanges.nyx.com/marisa-ricciardi/bio|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120607091053/http://exchanges.nyx.com/marisa-ricciardi/bio|archivedate=2012-06-07}}</ref>\n\nThrough the NYSE Global Partnership Program, NYSE Euronext has created a series of strategic resources to support its listed companies' growth initiatives, so as to act as a conduit that enables them to reach new and important audiences.<ref>{{cite web|title=Through the NYSE Global Partnership Program, we've created a series of strategic resources to support our listed companies' growth initiatives, and act as a conduit that enables them to reach new and important audiences. The NYSE Global Partnership Program is designed to provide our listed companies with a turnkey extension to their worldwide promotional and media relations activities.|url=https://www.nyse.com/about/listed/1224887730297.html|access-date=2017-09-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110703044410/http://www.nyse.com/about/listed/1224887730297.html|archive-date=2011-07-03|url-status=dead}}</ref> NYSE Euronext's 8,000 listed issues provide members with an extensive network of global investors and business leaders with which to interact. The company offers opportunities for co-branded advertising, linking listed companies to one another, as well as to the powerful brand that is NYSE Euronext.<ref>{{cite web|title=Strategic placement of corporate messaging will help extend the reach of your company's brand and its NYSE-listed status in an engaging way. Several opportunities are available for NYSE listed companies including subway, Times Square and Elevator advertising programs.|url=https://www.nyse.com/exccelerate/visibility/brand-activation.html|access-date=2017-09-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130526213153/http://www.nyse.com/exccelerate/visibility/brand-activation.html|archive-date=2013-05-26|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n===Events===\n\nThe [https://web.archive.org/web/20120219085114/http://www.nyx.com/eventrental/faq Events] department of NYSE Euronext is responsible for coordinating bell ceremonies, receptions, conferences, and street events. Beginning in 2010, the NYSE Euronext opened its doors to non-listed companies to utilize NYSE facilities for after-hours events.\n\n====Opening and closing ceremonies====\n\nThe opening and closing bell ceremonies hosted by the NYSE date back to 1903, taking place Monday through Friday at 9:30&nbsp;a.m. and 4:00&nbsp;p.m. respectively in New York City.\n\nThe opportunity to ring the bell at the New York Stock Exchange has long been considered an honor. Representatives from listed companies, especially newly listed companies and [[initial public offering|IPOs]], celebrities, politicians, and other dignitaries have become fixtures at the bell podium. Bell ceremonies are seen by millions, and are the most widely watched TV events each day.\n\nThe bell tradition has been extended to the branches in Paris, Brussels, and Lisbon. In Amsterdam, the opening bell was replaced by a [[gong]], which is sounded the signal the beginning and end of the trading day. In the European offices, the opening and closing ceremonies take place at 9:00&nbsp;a.m. and 5:30&nbsp;p.m., respectively.<ref>{{cite web|title=Bell ceremony overview|url=http://www.euronext.com/editorial/wide/editorial-21967-EN.html|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111207233945/http://www.euronext.com/editorial/wide/editorial-21967-EN.html|archivedate=2011-12-07}}</ref>\n\n====Experience Square====\nThe Broad Street area in front of the Exchange is known as Experience Square,{{citation needed|date=June 2015}} where listed companies are able to market themselves and their products directly to the thousands of visitors to New York's Financial District each day. The fa\u00e7ade of the exchange is often used as a billboard to showcase branding and new listings.{{citation needed|date=June 2015}}\n\n====''NYSE Magazine''====\n\n''NYSE Magazine'' is NYSE Euronext's quarterly publication. It provides insights into the world\u2019s best companies, giving readers a close-up look at the distinguished leaders who constitute the Exchange community. Written for a sophisticated audience of CEOs and other senior global executives, each issue centers on what makes companies succeed. Designed to foster a sense of community among the NYSE\u2019s key constituents, NYSE magazine has grown to become a strategic tool for business leaders that delivers opinions, strategies and insights from their peers. Extended articles, Q&As, videos, photo, and slideshows are now available at www.nysemagazine.com and on [[iPad]] via the NYSE magazine app. NYSE magazine print and digital editions reach thousands of opinion leaders around the globe, including top management of publicly traded and private companies, government officials, the financial community and the media.  NYSE ceased production of the print edition in 2013 and currently publishes content exclusively online.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|http://www.nyx.com/}}\n* [http://www.cbc.ca/news/story/2006/03/08/nyse-060308.html \"NYSE stock soars 25 per cent after it goes public for first time in 214 years\"], [[CBC News]], 2006-03-08\n\n{{NYSE Euronext}}\n{{Stock exchanges top 18}}\n{{World Federation of Exchanges}}\n{{Portal|Companies}}\n\n[[Category:Companies formerly listed on the New York Stock Exchange]]\n[[Category:NYSE Euronext| ]]\n[[Category:2007 establishments in New York City]]\n[[Category:Companies based in Manhattan]]\n[[Category:American companies established in 2007]]\n[[Category:Companies disestablished in 2013]]\n[[Category:Defunct companies of the United States]]\n[[Category:Financial services companies based in New York City]]\n[[Category:Multinational companies based in New York City]]\n[[Category:Options exchanges in the United States]]\n[[Category:2013 mergers and acquisitions]]\n[[Category:Companies formed by merger]]\n", "name_user": "MathXplore", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/NYSE_Euronext"}
{"title_page": "Minister of the Presidency of Costa Rica", "text_new": "{{Infobox Political post\n| insignia        = Coat of arms of Costa Rica.svg\n| insigniasize    = 125px\n |post            = Minister of the Presidency of Costa Rica\n |style           = \n |image           = File:No image.svg\n| imagesize       = 165px\n |incumbent       = Marcelo Prieto Jim\u00e9nez\n |incumbentsince  = 16 April 2020\n |formation       = \n |inaugural       = Mario Quir\u00f3s Sasso\n}}\nThe '''Ministry of the Presidency''' is a ministry of the [[Republic of Costa Rica]] created on 24 December 1961 through Law 2980.<ref>{{cite publication|last=Pallavicini|first=Violeta|title=El funcionamiento del alto gobierno en Costa Rica|url=http://siare.clad.org/siare/innotend/altogob/CostaRica.pdf|language=Spanish|access-date=2018-04-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150630082802/http://siare.clad.org/siare/innotend/altogob/CostaRica.pdf|archive-date=2015-06-30|url-status=dead}}</ref> Its work prescribed by law consists in providing support to the [[President of Costa Rica|President of the Republic]], serving as a liaison between the Presidency and the other [[branches of government]], [[civil society]] and the various ministries.\n\nBeing one of the most political ministries, since it has to coordinate with the social and political organizations, with the [[Legislative Assembly of Costa Rica|Legislative Assembly]] and with the opposition groups, it is usually put in charge of one of the closest collaborators of the President. The Costa Rican [[intelligence agency]], the Directorate of Intelligence and Security, reports to the Ministry of the Presidency,<ref>{{cite news|title=Reglamento de Organizaci\u00f3n y Funcionamiento de la Direcci\u00f3n de Inteligencia y Seguridad Nacional (Reglamenta la Direcci\u00f3n de Inteligencia y Seguridad Nacional indicada en el art\u00edculo 13 de la Ley N\u00b0 7410)|url=http://www.pgrweb.go.cr/scij/Busqueda/Normativa/Normas/nrm_texto_completo.aspx?param1=NRTC&nValor1=1&nValor2=55219&nValor3=60492&strTipM=TC|accessdate=28 April 2018|agency=SCIJ|date=27 May 1994|language=Spanish}}</ref> which has generated controversy.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Cambronero.|first1=Natasha|title=Defensora pide verificar si DIS tiene archivos de ciudadanos|url=https://www.nacion.com/el-pais/politica/defensora-pide-verificar-si-dis-tiene-archivos-de-ciudadanos/KSOMBDQYB5HJ3HYDPPAULWEWDY/story/|accessdate=28 April 2018|agency=La Naci\u00f3n|date=21 October 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Murillo|first1=\u00c1lvaro|last2=Vizca\u00edno|first2=Irene|title=Direcci\u00f3n de Inteligencia esp\u00eda sin ning\u00fan control|url=https://www.nacion.com/el-pais/direccion-de-inteligencia-espia-sin-ningun-control/D3F4YZKXMBB2BN2V3MD7NAO6NQ/story/|accessdate=28 April 2018|agency=La Naci\u00f3n|date=23 June 2008|language=Spanish}}</ref>\n\nSaid [[Portfolio (government)|portfolio]] is one of the most important in the Costa Rican presidential cabinet. The Minister of the Presidency has among its functions to coordinate inter-ministerial and inter-institutional work, to be an interlocutor between the President and the Parliament together with other tasks similar to those that in other countries fall on a [[Chief of Cabinet of Ministers|Chief of Cabinet]] or [[Prime Minister]], so usually a person of extreme confidence of the President is appointed. It is not unusual, too, that a few former presidential ministers have been later elected presidents of the Republic. The Minister of the Presidency, however, is not [[head of government]], as [[Constitution of Costa Rica|Costa Rica's Constitution]] establishes that the President is both [[head of state]] and head of government.<ref>{{cite news|title=CONSTITUCION POL \u00cd TICA DE COSTA RICA|url=http://pdba.georgetown.edu/Parties/CostaRica/Leyes/constitucion.pdf|accessdate=28 April 2018|agency=Georgetown University|date=7 November 1949|language=Spanish}}</ref> \n\nThe headquarters of the Ministry of the Presidency are located in Casa Presidencial in [[Zapote District, San Jos\u00e9]].\n\n==List of Ministers==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!colspan=9 style=\"background:#C0C0C0; color:#000000\"|Ministers of the Presidency \n|-\n! {{Abbr|No.|Number}}\n!colspan=2| Minister\n!Period\n!Party\n!colspan=3| President\n|-\n! style=\"background:{{National Liberation Party (Costa Rica)/meta/color}}| {{color|white|1}}  \n||<center>[[File:No_image.svg|50px]]</center>||Mario Quir\u00f3s Sasso||1962-1966<ref>{{cite book|last1=Rossi|first1=Jorge|title=La \"traici\u00f3n\" de los leales|publisher=EUNED|url=https://books.google.co.cr/books?id=w_R3HtGUkn4C&pg=PA143&lpg=PA143&dq=ministro+de+la+presidencia+de+don+chico+orlich&source=bl&ots=Q6Rf4VCsBK&sig=tw1_D9WJUe9LgxMg5KcLXG69lPQ&hl=es&sa=X&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=ministro%20de%20la%20presidencia%20de%20don%20chico%20orlich&f=false|access-date=30 November 2016|language=Spanish}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last1=L\u00f3pez Alfaro|first1=Salvador|last2=Fumero Paniagua|first2=Gerardo|title=TLC con Estados Unidos: desaf\u00edo al modelo solidario de Costa Rica|url=https://books.google.co.cr/books?id=KV1GGM0x7pAC&pg=PA249&lpg=PA249&dq=ministro+de+la+presidencia+mario+quir%C3%B3s+sasso&source=bl&ots=uqW87pzuua&sig=nWM4Hwsm5gTej3Gom4vVktogx7w&hl=es&sa=X&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=ministro%20de%20la%20presidencia%20mario%20quir%C3%B3s%20sasso&f=false|access-date=30 November 2016|language=Spanish}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=Directorio de Relaciones Oficiales No.|date=1965|url=https://books.google.co.cr/books?id=DpAgAQAAIAAJ&pg=PA34&lpg=PA34&dq=ministro+de+la+presidencia+mario+quir%C3%B3s+sasso&source=bl&ots=iDy9FnqC4u&sig=HhcmLvFx9e3qt5Yj-pmoynxqXbU&hl=es&sa=X&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=ministro%20de%20la%20presidencia%20mario%20quir%C3%B3s%20sasso&f=false|access-date=30 November 2016|language=Spanish}}</ref>\n||[[National Liberation Party (Costa Rica)|National Liberation Party]]\n! style=\"background:{{National Liberation Party (Costa Rica)/meta/color}